Combine all ingredients, including any blueberry juice, in a food processor. Buzz until smooth, and transfer to a serving dish. Pop in the freezer for a few minutes as the muffins bake, so the butter will firm up just a bit. Serve with the warm blueberry muffins and you almost won’t miss the fresh blueberries. Almost. Variation: Fresh Blueberry-Cream Cheese-Honeybutter Use ½ cup fresh blueberries in place of the thawed to raise the swoon factor. Serve on pancakes, waffles, or toast, or in crepes with whole fresh blueberries.